rComments: Great dude, we kind of got snaked because he only taught the first half of this course but that first half was amazing until we got Karen. If he is teaching a course individually, then that's great!

You're in luck if get Dr. Ratcliffe as a professor. He is able to explain the concepts clearly, concisely, and unambiguously which made studying for the course a breeze. As an added bonus he is an approachable, laid back, and pleasant individual. I wish he taught the second half of the course :( Favourite course quote: "That's an expensive word"
All around solid dude, had him for the first half of BIO328 & really appreciated him especially after getting Karen for the second half.

He's a great prof, you can tell he's passionate however, there's only pictures on his lecture slides theres no textbook and he talks fast and sometimes mixes up what he says. Tests are straight forward and easy. Assignment & presentation was brutal, no mercy when marking it. Material was SUPER easy to study. Very unorganized course though.
